      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTON REEVES (7) was in the money last time out when second and beaten 2 lengths at Ballarat over 545m (31.11). Has failed to finish in the placings from two starts here. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Sure to be about the mark. TIGER ROCKS (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (35.20) in a R/A FIN at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Goes well out of this box with a win and eight minor placings. Key player if finds best. SALT SPECKLE (2) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at Bendigo over 500m behind Flash Of Genius (28.17) in a Grade 4/5. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Should be thereabouts.",
